    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h2>Prerequisites</h2>

<p>According to the RVM guide, you need a few prerequisites to install Ruby:</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>sudo yum install curl wget git-core
</span><span class='line'>sudo yum install gcc zlib-devel make autoconf automake
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h2>Installing RVM</h2>

<p><a href="http://rvm.io/">RVM</a> is the Ruby Version Manager. RVM is a command-line tool which allows you to easily install, manage, and work with multiple ruby environments from interpreters to sets of gems.</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'><span class="se">\c</span>url -L https://get.rvm.io | bash -s stable --ruby
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h2>Installing Ruby</h2>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>Once Ruby is installed, ensure RVM has also installed the latest RubyGems:
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p> sh</p>

<pre><code>rvm install 1.9.3
rvm use 1.9.3
rvm rubygems latest
</code></pre>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>To check that it is properly installed, run these commands:
</span><span class='line'>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p> sh</p>

<pre><code>type rvm | head -1
# expected: rvm is a function
which rvm
# expected: ~/.rvm/bin/rvm
</code></pre>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>Installing Octopress
</span><span class='line'>--------------------
</span><span class='line'>Now that you have the system all configured, you<span class="err">&#39;</span>re almost all ready to begin the Octopress setup.  Simply change directories to a suitable location <span class="k">for </span>your site repository.
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p> sh
git clone git://github.com/imathis/octopress.git octopress
cd octopress    # If you use RVM, You&#8217;ll be asked if you trust the .rvmrc file (say yes).
ruby &#8211;version  # Should report Ruby 1.9.3</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>Next, install dependencies.
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p> sh
gem install bundler
bundle install</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>Install the default Octopress theme.
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p> sh
rake install</p>

